Morphology of a drug carrier is one of the most important parameters affecting the release behavior of the drug. As it can be seen (Fig. 4
                        ), addition of GQDs was altered the surface morphology of the beads. With increasing the GQDs nanoparticle contents, the aggregation phenomenon was observed. The high magnification SEM images show that the surface of the Cu-CMC and Cu-CMC/NPX/GQD hydrogel beads are highly wrinkled with many cavities in the internal zones. This structure could result in easier diffusion of water and PO4
                        3− into the beads and faster NPX release from the Cu-CMC/NPX/GQD.
